        <h4>Distance Learning Packets and Continuity of Learning and COVID-19 Response Plan</h4>

<p>April 20, 2020</p>

<p>In response to the technology survey, it has been decided that Central Montcalm can best meet the needs of our community by sending learning packets to all students in grades K-8. These were mailed today and should arrive soon.  Staff will be supporting the lessons in these packets through the Distance Learning Dashboards on each school's webpage.</p>

<p>We have also posted our Continuity of Learning and COVID-19 Response Plan on the front page of our District's website. You can also find it <a href="/downloads/district/cmps_continuity_of_learning_and_covid-19_response_plan_plan_application_1.pdf" target="_blank">here</a>.</p>

<p> </p>

<h4>Parent FAQ Regarding Covid-19 School Closure</h4>

<p>April 3, 2020</p>

<p>Yesterday, April 2, 2020, Governor Whitmer executed Executive Order 2020-35 closing all school buildings for the remainder of this school year. The CMPS administrative team has developed a document of Frequently Asked Questions for parents by parents.</p>

<p><a href="/downloads/district/parent_faq_regarding_covid-19_school_closure_4.pdf" target="_blank">Parent FAQ Regarding COVID-19 School Closure</a> - Updated 4/20/2020</p>

<p>We know many of you have questions about internet access and devices. We are still working on a plan.</p>

<p>If you are seeking low cost Internet options for your home during the time of COVID-19 school closure, the Michigan Department of Education has provided information found in the link below listing several options.  There are eligibility requirements with each option, most of which involve what school districts know as economically disadvantaged criteria.  This is also known as eligibility for free or reduced priced school meals.  Please feel free to share this information.</p>

<p><a href="http://Michigan%20Home%20Internet%20Options*%20for%20the%20Economically%20Disadvantaged" target="_blank">Michigan Home Internet Options* for the Economically Disadvantaged</a></p>

<h4> </h4>

<h4>Update from Superintendent Meinhardt</h4>

<p>March 31, 2020</p>

<p><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span>Dear families,</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>

<div><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></div>

<div><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span>I hope you are all doing as well as can be expected during a very difficult time. I would imagine many of you, like me, are feeling very overwhelmed with all of the information that we are receiving at a very rapid rate and wondering what is accurate and what is not.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></div>

<div><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></div>

<div><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span>On that note, many of you have seen headlines that Michigan has closed school for the rest of the year. <strong>The state has not given that directive to the schools.</strong> In a press conference on Monday, Governor Whitmer stated that she would be holding another press conference about education later in the week. I will certainly let you know as soon as I know anything official.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></div>

<div><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></div>

<div><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span>In the meantime, the administrators and teachers have been working very hard to put together supplemental learning activities that will be shared daily at every grade level starting April 7. You will find these lessons on your child's school webpage starting at <a href="https://central-montcalm.org/schools/" target="_blank">https://central-montcalm.org/schools/</a>. This will look different at every grade level. We will be sending home a bag with pencils, crayons and paper to support the learning activities if you need them. We will utilize our breakfast and lunch model to pass them out. If our supplies have arrived, we will hand them out during meal pick-up at the UE or drop them off during meal delivery starting April 6. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></div>

<div><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></div>

<div><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span>Drive-up at UE kitchen, 9-11, Monday, Wednesday and Friday ONLY</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></div>

<div><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span>Please email If you can't get to our location and need meals delivered to you, please email <a href="mailto:cmfood@central-montcalm.org" target="_blank">cmfood@central-montcalm.org</a> with your address and amount of meals needed for your kids.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></div>

<div><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></div>

<div><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span>Thank you for your quick response to the survey we sent out about your hardware and connectivity needs. We are working hard to make sure all students have access. Please be patient as this is a very challenging task and will take time. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></div>

<div><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></div>

<div><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span>Finally and most importantly, please take care of yourself. It is very important to us that all of our students have access to education but also care deeply about the social and emotional toll this is taking on them. Remember to take the time to talk and hang out with your kids. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></div>

<div><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></div>

<div><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span>I would like to send a thank-you out to all of the essential employees who are helping us through this challenging time. The businesses and employees still providing and delivering food, the administrators and directors packing and delivering breakfasts and lunches, the internet service providers and their employees for continuing to provide and hook-up our families so we can deliver content, and so many others. It takes a community to endure tough times and I am very happy to be part of this one!</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></div>

<div> </div>

<div>
<div>Amy Meinhardt
<div>Superintendent</div>

<div>Central Montcalm Public Schools</div>
</div>
</div>

<h4> </h4>

<h4>Back Door Lunches</h4>

<p>March 27, 2020</p>

<p>Free lunches will be made available on weekends from Noon-1 p.m. at Stanton First Congregational Church, 305 N. Camburn St., Stanton, MI 48888 (north side of the church) </p>

<h4> </h4>

<h4>CMPS Family Remote Learning Survey</h4>

<p>March 26, 2020</p>

<p>To begin to planning in case of an extended school closure, please provide us with the following information. Complete only one survey per household. Thank you.</p>

<p><a href="https://forms.gle/jnr595P7SxME11Xk6" target="_blank">https://forms.gle/jnr595P7SxME11Xk6</a></p>

<h4>Updated Student Resources Page for Learning at Home</h4>

<p>March 24, 2020</p>

<p>We wanted to let you know that we have updated our Central Montcalm Student Resources webpage. This page provides lots of valuable resources parents can use with their child to continue learning at home. Resources are divided into subjects. At the very bottom you’ll also find additional resources including schedules for learning at home.<br>
Go to <a href="http://central-Montcalm.org/resources/students" target="_blank">central-Montcalm.org/resources/students</a></p>

<h4>Update from Superintendent Meinhardt</h4>

<p>March 23, 2020</p>

<p>As you may have heard, the governor has issued a "Stay Home, Stay Safe" Executive Order. This order extends school closures through at least April 13, 2020. We have not been given any further information beyond that. We will keep you posted as we learn more. </p>

<p>We will still be providing breakfasts and lunches at this time as scheduled.</p>

<p>Please visit central-montcalm.org and click on the COVID-19 updates for more information.</p>

<h4>Feed America Food Truck Schedule</h4>

<p>March 23, 2020</p>

<p>Here is the schedule for the <img alt="External Link" class="externalLink" src="/Areas/Core/Images/icons/logo_link.png"><a href="https://www.feedwm.org/mobile-pantry-schedule/" target="_blank">Feed America Food Truck</a> for our area.</p>

<h4>Educational Resources for Students</h4>

<p>March 20, 2020</p>

<p>Click on the link below for several online educational resources that parents can use with their children. Check back often as we'll be adding more. Special thanks to our teachers for providing these links.</p>

<p><img alt="External Link" class="externalLink" src="/Areas/Core/Images/icons/logo_link.png"><a href="/resources/students/">Educational Resources for Students</a></p>

<p>If you have any questions, please contact Julie Milewski, Curriculum Director at<br>
jmilewski@central-montcalm.org</p>

<h4> </h4>

<h4>United Way 211</h4>

<p>March 19, 2020</p>

<p>United Way supports 211, a free and confidential service that helps people across North America find the local resources they need 24 hours a day, 7 days a week. If you need additional resources and support please dial 2-1-1 and United Way will connect you with organizations in our area.</p>

<h4> </h4>

<h4>CMPS Meat Up and Eat Up UPDATE</h4>

<p>March 19, 2020</p>

<p>We had a great first week of providing meals to our <span>CMPS</span> students. Special thanks to Food Service Director Amy Main and others for organizing all of these meals in these unique times. We will continue to provide meals Monday though Friday 9AM-11AM until April 5, 2020. We have a drive-thru service set up at Central Montcalm Upper Elementary and we will provide meals (breakfast and lunch) for all students 18 and under or 26 and under if they have a disability. </p>

<p>For preparation purposes, if you will be taking advantage of this opportunity we are asking families to sign up using this link: <a href="https://forms.gle/8hQ2Fd4Xgwphpg8eA">https://forms.gle/8hQ2Fd4Xgwphpg8eA</a></p>

<p>If you need meals delivered, please email <span>cmfood</span>@central-montcalm.org with MEALS in the subject line before 10 AM. Please provide us with your address and the number of students you need meals for. We are able to provide meals for multiple days.</p>

<p>Thank you. </p>

<h4><strong>CMPS Meet Up and Eat Up</strong></h4>

<p>March 13, 2020</p>

<p><span>To help keep our students fed, starting Tuesday, March 17th from 9:00am-10:30am meals will be available using a drive-up service for all students 18 and under.  These meals will be available for pick up on weekdays during the entire 3 week period (including CMPS Spring Break) at Central Montcalm Upper Elementary.  Please use the parent loop.</span></p>

<p>For preparation purposes, if you will be taking advantage of this opportunity we are asking families to sign up using this link: <a href="https://forms.gle/8hQ2Fd4Xgwphpg8eA">https://forms.gle/8hQ2Fd4Xgwphpg8eA</a></p>

